required_parameters.description: An array containing the IDs of the Droplets to be assigned to the Load Balancer instance..

api_list.name: addForwardingRulesToLoadBalancer
api_list.description: Add an additional forwarding rule to a Load Balancer instance.

required_parameters.name: entryPort
required_parameters.description: An integer representing the port on which the Load Balancer instance will listen.

required_parameters.name: targetPort
required_parameters.description: An integer representing the port on the backend Droplets to which the Load Balancer will send traffic.

required_parameters.name: entryProtocol
required_parameters.description: The protocol used for traffic to the Load Balancer. The possible values are: `http`, `https`, or `tcp`.

required_parameters.name: targetProtocol
required_parameters.description: The protocol used for traffic from the Load Balancer to the backend Droplets. The possible values are: `http`, `https`, or `tcp`.

optional_parameters.name: tlsPassthrough
optional_parameters.description: A boolean value indicating whether SSL encrypted traffic will be passed through to the backend Droplets. The defaults value is false.

optional_parameters.name: certificateId
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the TLS certificate to be used for SSL termination.

required_parameters.name: outboundRules

api_list.name: createDomain
api_list.description: Create a new domain.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: The domain name to add to the DigitalOcean DNS management interface. The name must be unique in DigitalOcean's DNS system. The request will fail if the name has already been taken.

required_parameters.name: ipAddress
required_parameters.description: This attribute contains the IP address you want the domain to point to.

api_list.name: createDomainRecord
api_list.description: Create an existing record.

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: The record type (A, MX, CNAME, AAAA, TXT, NS, SRV).

required_parameters.name: domain
required_parameters.description: The name of the domain itself. This should follow the standard domain format of domain.TLD. For instance, example.com is a valid domain name.

optional_parameters.name: weight
optional_parameters.description: The weight of records with the same priority (for SRV records only. null otherwise).

optional_parameters.name: port
optional_parameters.description: The port that the service is accessible on (for SRV records only. null otherwise).

optional_parameters.name: data
optional_parameters.description: Variable data depending on record type. See the [Domain Records]() section for more detail on each record type.

optional_parameters.name: name
optional_parameters.description: The host name, alias, or service being defined by the record.

optional_parameters.name: ttl
optional_parameters.description: This value is the time to live for the record, in seconds. This defines the time frame that clients can cache queried information before a refresh should be requested. If not set, the default value is 1800.

optional_parameters.name: priority
optional_parameters.description: The priority of the host (for SRV and MX records. null otherwise).

api_list.name: createDroplet
api_list.description: Create a new Droplet.

required_parameters.name: size
required_parameters.description: The unique slug identifier for the size that you wish to select for this Droplet. Example: 512mb

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: The human-readable string you wish to use when displaying the Droplet name. The name, if set to a domain name managed in the DigitalOcean DNS management system, will configure a PTR record for the Droplet. The name set during creation will also determine the hostname for the Droplet in its internal configuration.

required_parameters.name: image
required_parameters.description: The image ID of a public or private image, or the unique slug identifier for a public image. This image will be the base image for your Droplet. Example: ubuntu-14-04-x64

required_parameters.name: region
required_parameters.description: The unique slug identifier for the region that you wish to deploy in.

optional_parameters.name: monitoring
optional_parameters.description: A boolean indicating whether to install the DigitalOcean agent for monitoring.

optional_parameters.name: backups
optional_parameters.description: A boolean indicating whether automated backups should be enabled for the Droplet. Automated backups can only be enabled when the Droplet is created.

optional_parameters.name: privateNetworking
optional_parameters.description: A boolean indicating whether private networking is enabled for the Droplet. Private networking is currently only available in certain regions.

optional_parameters.name: ipv6
optional_parameters.description: A boolean indicating whether IPv6 is enabled on the Droplet.

optional_parameters.name: userData
optional_parameters.description: A string containing 'user data' which may be used to configure the Droplet on first boot, often a 'cloud-config' file or Bash script. It must be plain text and may not exceed 64 KiB in size.

optional_parameters.name: sshKeys
optional_parameters.description: An array containing the IDs or fingerprints of the SSH keys that you wish to embed in the Droplet's root account upon creation.

optional_parameters.name: volumes
optional_parameters.description: A flat array including the unique string identifier for each Block Storage volume to be attached to the Droplet. At the moment a volume can only be attached to a single Droplet.

optional_parameters.name: tags
optional_parameters.description: A flat array of tag names as strings to apply to the Droplet after it is created. Tag names can either be existing or new tags.

api_list.name: createLoadBalancer
api_list.description: Create a new Load Balancer instance.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: A human-readable name for a Load Balancer instance.

required_parameters.name: region
required_parameters.description: The region where the Load Balancer instance will be located. When setting a region, the value should be the slug identifier for the region. When you query a Load Balancer, an entire region object will be returned.

required_parameters.name: forwardingRules
required_parameters.description: An array of objects specifying the forwarding rules for a Load Balancer. At least one forwarding rule is required when creating a new Load Balancer instance (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: algorithm
optional_parameters.description: The load balancing algorithm used to determine which backend Droplet will be selected by a client. It must be either `round_robin` or `least_connections`. The default value is `round_robin`.

optional_parameters.name: redirectHttpToHttps
optional_parameters.description: A boolean value indicating whether HTTP requests to the Load Balancer on port 80 will be redirected to HTTPS on port 443. Default value is false.

optional_parameters.name: healthCheck
optional_parameters.description: An object specifying health check settings for the Load Balancer. If omitted, default values will be provided (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: stickySessions
optional_parameters.description: An object specifying sticky sessions settings for the Load Balancer (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: dropletIds
optional_parameters.description: An array containing the IDs of the Droplets to be assigned to the Load Balancer.

api_list.name: removeForwardingRulesFromLoadBalancer
api_list.description: Remove forwarding rules from a Load Balancer instance.

required_parameters.name: entryProtocol
required_parameters.description: The protocol used for traffic to the Load Balancer. The possible values are: `http`, `https`, or `tcp`.

required_parameters.name: targetProtocol
required_parameters.description: The protocol used for traffic from the Load Balancer to the backend Droplets. The possible values are: `http`, `https`, or `tcp`.

required_parameters.name: entryPort
required_parameters.description: An integer representing the port on which the Load Balancer instance will listen.

required_parameters.name: targetPort
required_parameters.description: An integer representing the port on the backend Droplets to which the Load Balancer will send traffic.

optional_parameters.name: certificateId
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the TLS certificate to be used for SSL termination.

optional_parameters.name: tlsPassthrough
optional_parameters.description: A boolean value indicating whether SSL encrypted traffic will be passed through to the backend Droplets. The defaults value is false.

api_list.name: updateDomainRecord
api_list.description: Update an existing record.

required_parameters.name: recordId
required_parameters.description: A unique identifier for each domain record.

required_parameters.name: domain
required_parameters.description: The name of the domain itself. This should follow the standard domain format of domain.TLD. For instance, example.com is a valid domain name.

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: The name of the domain itself. This should follow the standard domain format of domain.TLD. For instance, example.com is a valid domain name.

optional_parameters.name: name
optional_parameters.description: The host name, alias, or service being defined by the record.

optional_parameters.name: ttl
optional_parameters.description: This value is the time to live for the record, in seconds. This defines the time frame that clients can cache queried information before a refresh should be requested. If not set, the default value is 1800.

optional_parameters.name: priority
optional_parameters.description: The priority of the host (for SRV and MX records. null otherwise).

optional_parameters.name: port
optional_parameters.description: The port that the service is accessible on (for SRV records only. null otherwise).

optional_parameters.name: weight
optional_parameters.description: The weight of records with the same priority (for SRV records only. null otherwise).

optional_parameters.name: data
optional_parameters.description: Variable data depending on record type. See the [Domain Records]() section for more detail on each record type.

api_list.name: updateFirewall

required_parameters.name: firewallId
required_parameters.description: A unique ID that can be used to identify and reference a Firewall.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: A human-readable name for a Firewall.

required_parameters.name: inboundRules
required_parameters.description: An object specifying the inbound access rules for a Firewall (see example below).

required_parameters.name: outboundRules
required_parameters.description: An object specifying the outbound access rules for a Firewall (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: dropletIds
optional_parameters.description: An array containing the IDs of the Droplets to be assigned to the Firewall.

optional_parameters.name: tags
optional_parameters.description: An array containing the names of the Tags to be assigned to the Firewall..

api_list.name: updateLoadBalancer
api_list.description: Update a Load Balancer's settings.

required_parameters.name: name
required_parameters.description: A human-readable name for a Load Balancer instance.

required_parameters.name: region
required_parameters.description: The region where the Load Balancer instance will be located. When setting a region, the value should be the slug identifier for the region. When you query a Load Balancer, an entire region object will be returned.

required_parameters.name: forwardingRules
required_parameters.description: An array of objects specifying the forwarding rules for a Load Balancer. At least one forwarding rule is required when creating a new Load Balancer instance (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: algorithm
optional_parameters.description: The load balancing algorithm used to determine which backend Droplet will be selected by a client. It must be either `round_robin` or `least_connections`. The default value is `round_robin`.

optional_parameters.name: redirectHttpToHttps
optional_parameters.description: A boolean value indicating whether HTTP requests to the Load Balancer on port 80 will be redirected to HTTPS on port 443. Default value is false.

optional_parameters.name: tag
optional_parameters.description: The name of a Droplet tag corresponding to Droplets to be assigned to the Load Balancer.

optional_parameters.name: healthCheck
optional_parameters.description: An object specifying health check settings for the Load Balancer. If omitted, default values will be provided (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: stickySessions
optional_parameters.description: An object specifying sticky sessions settings for the Load Balancer (see table below).

optional_parameters.name: dropletIds
optional_parameters.description: An array containing the IDs of the Droplets to be assigned to the Load Balancer.
